title: Architectural Model, "Sudbury Hall", ca. 1660-90
provenance: 2012, from Eugene V. and Clare Thaw, who acquired it in England from an antiques fair ca 1980.
dimensions:
Base: H x W x D: 30.5 x 69.2 x 35.6 cm (12 in. x 27 1/4 in. x 14 in.)
House: H x W x D: 30.5 x 49.5 x 25.4 cm (12 in. x 19 1/2 in. x 10 in.)
creditline: Gift of Eugene V. and Clare E. Thaw
description:
in the form of Sudbury Hall, Derbyshire, an English country house of c. 1665-early 1690's, a rectangle with protruding central entrances and end wings, a central domed cupola and rectangular chimneys on the main block and two at each end,
with small dormer windows above the two floors, delineated by a line of moulding.

tombstone.epitaph:
Architectural Model, "Sudbury Hall", ca. 1660-90.
ca. 1660-90. stained pine. Gift of Eugene V. and Clare E. Thaw. 2013-3-5.
